# An unknown string escape -- here `\ ` (backslash-space) -- is invalid: only
# \n \t \\ \" are valid string escapes. hierc rejected this at lex time, but
# hierc0 silently ACCEPTED it (fail-open: it skipped the escaped byte without
# validating, then emitted a C string literal gcc would mangle). The reject-fuzzer
# surfaced it as an accept/reject divergence (divergence_6). Both lexers now reject.
fn main():
    print("oops\ here\n")
